You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput microservice migrated to Java 21 Virtual Threads experiences severe throughput degradation and thread starvation under load. Profiling reveals the following code block is frequently executed:

java
public class DataIngestionService {
    private final ReentrantLock lock = new ReentrantLock();

    public synchronized String fetchAndProcess(String sourceUrl) {
        // Simulating external network call
        try {
            Thread.sleep(200);
            return "Data from " + sourceUrl;
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue in a Spring Boot application where database writes initiated within a `CompletableFuture` chain are persisting even when the enclosing transactional method fails and rolls back. The service layer is defined as follows:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired
    private OrderRepository orderRepository;
    @Autowired
    private AuditLogRepository auditLogRepository;
    @Autowired
    private Executor asyncExecutor;

    @Transactional
    public void placeOrder(Order order) {
        orderRepository.save(order);

        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            auditLogRepository.save(new AuditLog("Order initiated"));
        }, asyncExecutor);

        if (true) { 
            throw new RuntimeException("Simulated database failure"); 
        }
    }
}
